House Resolution 720
By: Representatives Myles of the 126th and Howard of the 129th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Alfonzo Williams; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Alfonzo Williams has served with honor and distinction as the Sheriff of Burke
3 County since 2017; and
4 WHEREAS, Sheriff Williams has over 35 years of law enforcement experience, and made
5 history as the first African American Sheriff of Burke County and the first African American
6 Police Chief of the City of Waynesboro Police Department; and
7 WHEREAS, he is an honest and dedicated public servant who strives for excellence in all
8 of his endeavors and whose primary concern is the welfare and safety of the citizens of
9 Georgia; and
10 WHEREAS, he is highly regarded by the citizens of his community and by state and local
11 government officials as a man of unquestioned integrity and dedication to the administration
12 of justice and sound principles of law enforcement; and
