13 WHEREAS, this spirited law enforcement professional has exhibited extraordinary devotion
14 to duty, outstanding loyalty, fine leadership, and meticulous attention to detail in all of his
15 duties; and
16 WHEREAS, Sheriff Williams' efficient and effective commitment to excellence has been
17 recognized by his peers through the many decorations and awards he has received, including
18 several Officer of the Year awards; and
19 WHEREAS, his inspiring commitment to the welfare of others is an outstanding example of
20 the positive effect law enforcement professionals have on the lives and well-being of others;
21 and
22 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that gratitude is expressed for the unique and
23 often unheralded contributions of local law enforcement professionals on behalf of the
24 citizens of this state.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body commend the care, courage, sympathy, and selfless dedication
27 exhibited by Alfonzo Williams in carrying out the difficult duties of his vocation and express
28 their utmost appreciation for having so purely and truly defined for others the meaning of
29 public servant.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
32 Alfonzo Williams.
